2026-03-08 | Find Unique Binary String

	Question
Given n unique binary strings of length n, construct a binary string of length n that does not appear in nums.

	Approach
1.	Use Cantor’s Diagonalization idea.
2.	Construct a new string by flipping the diagonal characters.
3.	For each index i:
		if nums[i][i] == '0'
			put '1'
		else
			put '0'
4.	This guarantees the new string differs from every nums[i] at position i.
5.	Therefore the constructed string cannot match any string in nums.

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(n)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    string findDifferentBinaryString(vector<string>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        string result = "";

        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (nums[i][i] == '0')
                result += '1';
            else
                result += '0';
        }

        return result;
    }
};

	Key Insight
By flipping the i-th character of the i-th string,
the constructed string differs from every input string at least at one position.
This guarantees the new string is not present in the array.
